Introduction

This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile). You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).

Base URL

localhost:8080

Authenticating requests

This API is not authenticated.

Authenticatie

Basic login

This is used for first time authentication.

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "localhost:8080/authentication" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"email\": \"development@dxmusic.nl\",
    \"password\": \"password\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "localhost:8080/authentication"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "email": "development@dxmusic.nl",
    "password": "password"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{
    "token": "String"
}

Example response (401):


"error": {
 "code": 401,
 "message": "Invalid credentials."
}

Example response (429):


"error": {
 "code": 429,
 "message": "Too Many Attempts."
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:

Request      

POST authentication

Body Parameters

email  string  

E-mail of the user.

password  string  

Password of the user.

Renew token

requires authentication

With this endpoint you can request a new token, the current one should be valid.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "localhost:8080/authentication/jwt" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "localhost:8080/authentication/jwt"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Example response (200):


{
    "token": "String"
}

Example response (401):


"error": {
 "code": 401,
 "message": "Unauthorized."
}

Example response (429):


"error": {
 "code": 429,
 "message": "Too Many Attempts."
}
Received response:
Request failed with error:

User management

API's for managing users

Show my user profile

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "localhost:8080/users" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "localhost:8080/users"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());

Request      

GET users

Weather Data

API's for everything related to weather data and stations.

Send weather data to backend

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "localhost:8080/stations/sendWeatherData" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"WEATHERDATA\": [
        \"100020\",
        \"1970-01-01 00:00\",
        10,
        10,
        10,
        10,
        10,
        10,
        10,
        10,
        [
            0,
            0,
            0,
            0,
            0,
            0
        ]
    ]
}"

const url = new URL(
    "localhost:8080/stations/sendWeatherData"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "WEATHERDATA": [
        "100020",
        "1970-01-01 00:00",
        10,
        10,
        10,
        10,
        10,
        10,
        10,
        10,
        [
            0,
            0,
            0,
            0,
            0,
            0
        ]
    ]
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

GET stations/getWeatherData

Get a list of available stations.

Example request:
curl --request GET \
    --get "localhost:8080/stations/getStations" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"page\": 1,
    \"ordered_row\": \"temp\",
    \"order_by\": \"asc\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "localhost:8080/stations/getStations"
);

const headers = {
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "page": 1,
    "ordered_row": "temp",
    "order_by": "asc"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "GET",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());
